<tr id="L297"><td><a href="#L297">297</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Spock, I know it's a terrible personal lowering of mental barriers but if there's a chance</td></tr>

<tr id="L298"><td><a href="#L298">298</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I'll try.</td></tr>

<tr id="L299"><td><a href="#L299">299</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He fastens his phaser to his belt and carefully approaches the worried creature. Without touching, he concentrates for a moment and then cries out.</td></tr>

<tr id="L300"><td><a href="#L300">300</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Pain! Pain! Pain! (he staggers back) That's all I got, Captain. Waves and waves of searing pain. It's in agony.</td></tr>

